    {
      "type": "teach",
      "title": "Ligatures of sound",
      "body": "𐑿 and 𐑾 are ligatures too, but of sounds rather than an r: 𐑿 packs “y”+“oo” into one letter (few is f-yoo), and 𐑾 glides “i” into “a”. That completes the whole ligature family — the eight r-vowels plus these two. Only four ordinary vowels remain before you know the full alphabet."
